26/08/2009
OTTAWA, Canada -- Macedonian Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski kicked off a four-day visit to Canada on Tuesday (August 25th) at the invitation of counterpart Stephen Harper.
Gruevski will meet with parliamentary and government officials to discuss ways to strengthen bilateral relations, especially economic ties, as well as Macedonia's NATO bid.
(MIA, MRT, Sitel, Makfax - 25/08/09)
